The support of `($ᵗ α)` and `($ᵗ β)` are `Set.univ` (from `support_uniformSample`).
The distribution `selectElem` is the product distribution, so its support is the Cartesian product of the supports, which is `Set.univ ×ˢ Set.univ = Set.univ`.
To prove `x ∈ Set.univ`, we simply need to show `True`, but `simp` might get stuck on the structure of the support set (expressed as `image` or `bind`). Destructing `x` into components `(a, b)` allows `simp` to match the structure of the product constructor in the definition of `selectElem`.

